<i>noun</i>: 화술 [화술], 장광설 [장광설], 입심 [입씸], 웅변 [웅변], 언변 [언변], 말발 [말ː빨], 능변 [능변], 구변 [구ː변] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화술 [화술]</dt><br>
<dd>art of talk; gift of gab; eloquence</dd><br>
<dd>말을 잘하는 재주나 기술.</dd><br>
<dd>A talent or art of speaking well.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>장광설 [장광설]</dt><br>
<dd>1. eloquence</dd><br>
<dd>막힘없이 길게 잘하는 말솜씨.</dd><br>
<dd>The skill of speaking fluently for a long time.</dd><br>
<dd>2. rambling</dd><br>
<dd>쓸데없이 길게 늘어놓는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A long, meaningless speech.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>입심 [입씸]</dt><br>
<dd>eloquence</dd><br>
<dd>막힘없이 쉬지 않고 말하는 힘.</dd><br>
<dd>The ability to speak well and fluently.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>웅변 [웅변]</dt><br>
<dd>1. oratory; eloquence</dd><br>
<dd>체계적이고 논리적으로 막힘이 없이 힘이 있게 하는 말이나 연설.</dd><br>
<dd>A fluent utterance or speech that is organized, logical, and powerful.</dd><br>
<dd>2. being clear; being certain</dd><br>
<dd>의심할 것 없이 아주 뚜렷함.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being certain without any doubt.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>언변 [언변]</dt><br>
<dd>eloquence; gift of gab</dd><br>
<dd>말을 잘하는 솜씨.</dd><br>
<dd>A skill of speaking well.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>말발 [말ː빨]</dt><br>
<dd>eloquence</dd><br>
<dd>듣는 사람을 그 말대로 따르게 하는 말의 힘.</dd><br>
<dd>The power of one's words that makes the listener follow them.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>능변 [능변]</dt><br>
<dd>1. eloquence; fluency</dd><br>
<dd>말을 능숙하게 잘함. 또는 그 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of talking fluently; or the talk.</dd><br>
<dd>2. eloquent speaker; fluent speaker</dd><br>
<dd>말을 능숙하게 잘하는 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who talks fluently.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>구변 [구ː변]</dt><br>
<dd>eloquence</dd><br>
<dd>말을 잘하는 재주.</dd><br>
<dd>A talent of speaking well.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>